What you need to know:  Differences between leaders and residents over the location of a referral hospital to be constructed by the national government in the South Rift region have deepened, jeopardising the project.Leaders from Kericho, Bomet and Narok counties, which are set to benefit from the project, have for the last two months been engaged in a back-and-forth.Senate Majority Leader Aaron Cheruiyot and Kipkelion East MP Joseph Cherorot are some of the leaders spearheading the push to have the hospital constructed in Londiani.